                  , on the <rs id="t18331128-162-cd904" type="crimeDate">24th of November</rs>
                     <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18331128-162-off903 t18331128-162-cd904"></join>, and stealing 5 live tame fowls, value 5s., his property
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>WILLIAM LUMLEY. I live in <placeName id="t18331128-162-crimeloc905">Cottage-place, City-road. It is my dwelling-house, and is in the parish of St. Luke</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18331128-162-crimeloc905" type="placeName" value="Cottage-place, City-road. It is my dwelling-house, and is in the parish of St. Luke"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18331128-162-crimeloc905" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18331128-162-off903 t18331128-162-crimeloc905"></join>. I keep fowls, but I was ill in bed at the time these were stolen - I know they are mine.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18331128-162-person1639">
                  JOHN 
                  SAPTHORNE
               <interp inst="t18331128-162-person1639" type="surname" value="SAPTHORNE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18331128-162-person1639" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18331128-162-person1639" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             (police-constable G 182). On the 24th of November, I was on duty, in Goswell-street, at half-past three o'clock in the morning. I saw the prisoner with a bag in his hand - I stopped him, and asked what he had - he said, "Some fowls" - I asked him to allow me to look at them - I took them in my hand, and asked where he brought them from - he said from Finchley, and was going to take them to his brother in Old-street - I said I would go with him; I went with him to the end of Gee-street - he then ran away - I followed him - he ran on to the Willow-walk; I took him there - I asked him how many fowls there were; he said four, and he gave 4s. for them, to a man on the road.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. STAMMERS. Q. The fowls were in a bag? A. Yes.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18331128-162-person1640">
                  SARAH 
                  BUTLER
               <interp inst="t18331128-162-person1640" type="surname" value="BUTLER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18331128-162-person1640" type="given" value="SARAH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18331128-162-person1640" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I live with Mr. Lumley my brother-in-law. There are three gates in the garden, which lead to the poultry-house, but that does not join to the dwelling-house - on Saturday week, at nine o'clock in the evening, I shut the poultry-house up secure, and these fowls were missed the next morning - I knew the prisoner - he has occasionally worked as gardener for my brother.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined. Q. Were you in the habit of feeding them? A. Yes; very often - there was a padlock on the door of the fowl-house - the outer gate of the yard was shut the night before, but in the morning it was open.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I am a pork-butcher, and went down to Finchley for work, and on coming back I met a man, who said, "Will you purchase these fowls?" He asked 5s. for them, I gave him 4s.; I came on towards home, and was stopped by the policeman; I told him what I had got, and walked a few paces with him, but being agitated I ran away; I was then taken to the station-house. I was taken to the magistrate, who, having a good character of me from Mr. Stroud, and Mr. Van, the officers; gave me up, till the following Tuesday; I went to work, and was taken again.</p>
               <p>GUILTY of Stealing only. Aged 21. - <rs id="t18331128-162-verdict906" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18331128-162-verdict906" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18331128-162-verdict906" type="verdictSubcategory" value="withRecommendation"></interp>
               Recommended to Mercy by the Prosecutor
            </rs> - <rs id="t18331128-162-punish907" type="punishmentDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18331128-162-punish907" type="punishmentCategory" value="imprison"></interp>
                     <join result="defendantPunishment" targOrder="Y" targets="t18331128-162-defend1636 t18331128-162-punish907"></join>
               Confined Six Months
            </rs>.</p>
